---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const environments = [
  { label: "Courtyard", href: "https://guestexp360.com/cy" },
  { label: "SpringHill Suites", href: "https://guestexp360.com/shs" },
  { label: "Four Points", href: "https://guestexp360.com/fp" },
  { label: "Fairfield", href: "https://guestexp360.com/ff" },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Marriott 360° AR Experience"
  description="A WebVR experience for a Marriott conference — 360° panoramic hotel tours, scaled to ~1,000 concurrent users."
>
  <article class="document">
    <p class="label" data-animate>
      <a href="/fun" class="back">← Fun stuff</a>
    </p>
    <h1 data-animate>Marriott 360° AR Experience</h1>
    <hr class="rule" data-animate />

    <p data-animate>
      In 2019 I worked with Marriott to create an augmented reality experience
      for a conference they were hosting. The goal was a mobile-friendly site
      where users could view 360° panoramic photos of various hotel rooms —
      photos that could then be viewed through a VR headset such as Google
      Cardboard or Oculus.
    </p>
    <p data-animate>
      I built the front-end in React and hosted it on Zeit so I could scale up
      quickly — at peak there were up to 1,000 active users in the VR experience
      at the same time. I implemented some backend work with Firebase, plus
      Google Analytics tracking. The WebVR technology is built on A-Frame, an
      open-source, cross-platform web VR framework.
    </p>
    <p data-animate>
      The site was initially built for Courtyard only, but after its success I
      was asked to build out separate environments for SpringHill Suites, Four
      Points, and Fairfield.
    </p>

    <h2 data-animate>Explore the environments</h2>
    <ul class="env-list" data-animate>
      {
        environments.map((env) => (
          <li>
            <a href={env.href} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              {env.label} ↗
            </a>
          </li>
        ))
      }
    </ul>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .back {
    border-bottom: none;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
  }
  .back:hover {
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .env-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin-left: 0;
  }
</style>
